mobility’s predecessor company bell cellular he served as president of bell distribution inc since august   he is a year veteran of the telecom industry he was instrumental in the national build outs of two fastgrowing wireless carriers clearnet and telus mobility mr oosterman honored his expertise in driving both revenues and cost efficiencies at the executive level with national wireless carrier clearnet communications where he served as executive vicepresident of sales and marketing until  he served as an executive vicepresident sales and marketing for telus mobility mr oosterman served as an executive vice president and chief marketing officer of telus corporation mr oosterman began his career in telecommunications as an executive with bell cellular distribution services inc he serves as a director of the foundation fighting blindness  canada and the toronto international film festival he served as an independent director of ingram micro inc from september   to december   he served as a director of the investment fund for foundations he served as a board member at clearnet communications until  he serves as a director of the foundation fighting blindness canada he is recognized for his focus on profitable growth having developed pricing and product strategies that translated into industryleading revenue earnings and cash flow growth for the two carriers he holds a master of business administration degree from the university of western ontario’s ivey school of business he holds a bachelor of arts degree in economics and finance from the university of western ontarioread full background corporate headquarters  carrefour alexandergrahambellverdun quebec he bcanadaphone fax  board members memberships there is no board members memberships data available education ba the university of western ontariomba university of western ontario ivey school of business other affiliations clearnet communications incingram micro incbell canada incbell mobility inctelus corporationth